# Vue: Composition API only

All new Vue single-file components MUST use the Composition API with
`<script setup lang="ts">`. Do not use the Options API (`data()`, `methods`,
`computed`, `watch`, `mounted`, etc.) in new code.

## Rules

- Use `<script setup lang="ts">` — no `export default { ... }` blocks.
- Reactive state: `ref`, `reactive`, `computed`, `watch`, `watchEffect`.
- Component props: `defineProps<{...}>()` (type-based, no runtime declarations).
- Events: `defineEmits<{...}>()`.
- Two-way binding: `defineModel<T>()` over manual `modelValue` + `update:modelValue`.
- Lifecycle: `onMounted`, `onUnmounted`, etc. — never `mounted()` / `beforeDestroy()`.
- Extract reusable stateful logic into `src/composables/useX.ts`.
- Keep `<template>` first and `<style>` last is fine, but `<script setup>` must
  be present in every new SFC.

## Examples

### Good

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
import { computed, ref } from 'vue'

const props = defineProps<{ initial?: number }>()
const emit = defineEmits<{ change: [value: number] }>()

const count = ref(props.initial ?? 0)
const doubled = computed(() => count.value * 2)

function increment() {
  count.value += 1
  emit('change', count.value)
}
</script>

<template>
  <button type="button" @click="increment">{{ count }} (×2 = {{ doubled }})</button>
</template>
```

### Bad — Options API (do not use for new components)

```vue
<script lang="ts">
import { defineComponent } from 'vue'

export default defineComponent({
  props: { initial: { type: Number, default: 0 } },
  data() {
    return { count: this.initial }
  },
  computed: {
    doubled() {
      return this.count * 2
    },
  },
  methods: {
    increment() {
      this.count += 1
      this.$emit('change', this.count)
    },
  },
})
</script>
```

## When editing existing Options-API components

If a file already uses the Options API, prefer migrating it to `<script setup>`
when making non-trivial changes; for tiny fixes, match the existing style and
note that a follow-up migration is desirable.
